Here discontented Beauty pined away, And vainly conscious asked her promised sway;
Here Luxury prepared his sumptuous feast, While lurking Apathy behind him lay To poison all the insipid food he drest, And shake his poppy crown o'er every sated guest.
The hireling minstrels strke their weary lyre, And slumber o'er the oft-repeated strain;
No listless youth to active grace they fire :
Here Eloquence herself might plead in vain, Nor one of all the heartless crowd could gain:
